    %h1.heading Altimarc Refund Policy
.row
  .span12{:style => 'padding-bottom: 200px;'}
    %p
      %strong 30 days free on a new pay account.
    %p Altimarc products offer a free 30-day trial on new pay accounts (Personal, Basic, Plus, Premium, and Max). Upgrades from free accounts do not qualify for the free 24-hour trial. If you upgrade from a free to a paying account you’ll be charged for your first month when you upgrade.
    %p
      %strong Cancel within the first 24 hours and you won’t be charged.
    %p If you cancel your paid account before you are billed 24 hours after your original signup then you won’t be charged.
    %p
      %strong Cancel after 24 hours and you won’t be charged again.
    %p
      Once you cancel you won’t be charged again,
      %em but you are responsible for whatever charges have already been incurred for the current billing period.
      For example, if your billing cycle is on the 18th of every month, and you cancel on the 24th, you’ll still have to pay for the current month, but you won’t be charged again after that. In order to treat everyone equally, no exceptions will be made.
    %p
      %strong How do I cancel my account?
    %p You can cancel your account at any time by logging into your account and selecting the “Account” tab (usually found on the Dashboard). Once you are on the Account page, click the “Please cancel my account” link.
